name: Laphonza Butler
content: I'm honored to accept Gov. Gavin Newsom's nomination to be U.S. Senator for a state I have made my home and honored by his trust in me to serve the people of California and this great nation. No one will ever measure up to the legacy of Sen. Dianne Feinstein, but I will do my best to honor her legacy and leadership by committing to work for women and girls, workers and unions, struggling parents, and all of California. I am ready to serve.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: 3 years ago today, Kamala Harris made history by becoming Joe Biden's running mate. The first Black woman and first woman of South Asian descent to join a major-party ticket. Let me tell you a bit about the Vice President I know — an inspiration and a fearless fighter for our freedoms. I've often found myself saying there's no one who has done the job that she is being asked to do. As the first woman of color to serve as Vice President, Kamala Harris is in a league of her own. There was no blueprint. She is creating it. That is life-changing for so many of us. Beyond her mere presence, we need to talk about her work, which is fundamentally changing peoples' lives. Since joining the Biden-Harris ticket 3 years ago, she has been a fearless and effective messenger in calling out the Republican agenda and fighting for the American people. Kamala Harris is a historic, forceful leader and partner to Joe Biden — at the forefront of our fight for our democracy and freedom. Since Dobbs, the Vice President has been leading the administration's response, meeting with advocates, doctors, and women across over 20 states and close to 50 meetings. Kamala Harris has been a leading voice in the fight against gun violence, helping to lead the admin's push for gun safety measures. As Vice President, she has traveled to communities shaken by tragedy and recently met with the Tennessee 3 who protested gun violence on the chamber floor. Kamala Harris has been a champion in the fight for our democracy and future generations — from the right to vote for all Americans, to the freedom to teach American’s full history, to demanding action on gun violence and standing with lawmakers fighting for their communities. Kamala Harris has been a champion for climate action and environmental justice. The Vice President cast the tie-breaking vote on the Inflation Reduction Act, the most significant climate bill ever. In 2023 alone, she has held 23 climate events in 10 states, centering communities of color.Kamala Harris has met with over 100 world leaders and traveled to 18 countries to strengthen our alliances and partnerships around the world—with a particular emphasis on Southeast Asia, the Caribbean, and Africa. Like so many, I was deeply moved by her remarks in South Africa.This is not an exhaustive list. I could go on, and over the next 14 months, EMILYs List will make the case for why Kamala Harris deserves 4 more years. Today we're launching our Madam Vice President campaign to do just that — follow along and ask the joyful warriors you know to do the same.Let me close with this: I've known Kamala Harris for a long time. I know her commitment to showing up and fighting for the American people. I know her heart. I know that my young daughter, all of our daughters, have a champion in this Vice President. And we are all better off because of it.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Black women experience maternal mortality at a rate higher than any other group – a fact that was rarely addressed by the government until Black women leaders raised their voices in office. When coupled with Republican attacks on reproductive health care that disproportionately affect women of color, it has never been more important to take action to ensure Black mothers feel safe and supported throughout their birthing experience. Black Mamas Matter Alliance founded Black Maternal Health Week to fill that gap and center the voices of Black women in the fight for reproductive health equity. At EMILYs List, we are grateful for the Black women leaders whose presence in office ensures that this issue is finally being addressed. We also remain committed to increasing representation in all levels of government, because when women run, they do so with the collective power and support of their community. And when in office, they change the world.

content: The transgender and nonbinary communities are filled with individuals who are brave, resilient, and powerful. In the face of so many roadblocks, they choose to be true to themselves, oftentimes confronting real danger from bigoted individuals who threaten their safety. They continue to live authentically, and battle anti-trans bigotry with a grace that belies their strength. We celebrate Trans Day of Visibility with them – recognizing that with the joy comes the knowledge that there is still much work to do.We are proud to support Democratic pro-choice transgender women who run for office, fighting back against the Republicans who are attempting to legislate away their very existence. EMILYs List is committed to lifting up their voices, and ensuring that the halls of power are filled with politicians who are truly representative of their communities. On this day, and every other, we see you. We celebrate you. And we will stand with you until true equity is achieved, and trans people can live the lives they deserve, free of discrimination.

name: Laphonza Butler

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Today, the Supreme Court overturned Roe v. Wade, undoing nearly 50 years of precedent and taking direct aim at our freedom. They have effectively outlawed the freedom to make our own health care decisions and the freedom that allows us the opportunity to decide our own future.This court is moving us backward, taking rights away and giving control of our bodies and our decisions to the government.This decision was made by a handful of justices, most nominated by a president who lost the popular vote and voted in by senators representing less than half of the population, despite the fact that the majority of this country supports the freedom afforded by Roe v. Wade.Their decision will have sweeping consequences for millions of Americans.Republicans have fought to undermine reproductive rights for decades, and as devastating as this decision is, it won’t be the end of their effort. In states around the country, Republicans are advancing more extreme restrictions to criminalize abortion & punish women and doctors.Republican groups and party leaders have already made clear their intention to pass a national abortion ban. If they get their way, even states that have codified access to abortion will be forced to stop care. They will not stop until they replace our freedom with their control.Make no mistake: abortion is on the ballot this November, and we, the pro-choice majority in this country, will hold them accountable.We will replace them in offices across the country, up and down the ballot with Democratic pro-choice candidates who will fight for our rights and freedom, with women who will work to expand access to anyone who needs it.Today is a tragic day. But this decision will not end the debate on this issue. We will take this fight to the ballot box. We are the majority in this country and we will fight back.Join us: https://win.emilyslist.org/a/20220617_social_postdobbs

Karen Bass, Maitreyi Ramakrishnan, Robin Thede, and Yvette Nicole Brown, for your support for the work we're doing at EMILY's List! It was a pleasure speaking today about the collective power of women to make transformative change happen. Also, thank you Amber Tamblyn, for your role in the event and the great photo. Check out EMILY’s List on Instagram for video recaps of the event.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: November is going to be here before we know it. The time to invest in these Democratic pro-choice champions – who can protect and expand our hard-earned Democratic House majority – is now.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: So excited for tomorrow’s event featuring these amazing women: Amber Tamblyn, Bozoma Saint John, Chiney Ogwumike, Gloria Calderón Kellett, Rep. Karen Bass, Maitreyi Ramakrishnan, Robin Thede, and Yvette Nicole Brown!

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Judge Jackson’s presence on the highest court in the land would symbolize something that the entire EMILY's List team, including myself, fight for every day – representation.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Join us tomorrow in front of the Supreme Court to show support for Judge Ketanji Brown Jackson’s historic nomination!

name: Laphonza Butler
content: I side with teachers seeking adequate pay and vital mental health supports in schools! ​

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Happy Holi to all who celebrate!

name: Laphonza Butler
content: The Asian-American community has seen an increase in hate crimes and violence since the start of the pandemic. We cannot allow fear, ignorance, and racism to take hold. We stand with women endorsed by EMILY’s List who are fighting to keep their communities safe. #StopAsianHate

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Join us outside the Supreme Court on March 21 to center joy and celebrate Judge Ketanji Brown Jackson’s history-making nomination to SCOTUS! This looks like it’s going to be a wonderful event!

name: Laphonza Butler
content: I’m really looking forward to this event. Follow EMILY’s List on Instagram to see highlights and live video.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Judge Ketanji Brown Jackson is ready and capable of handling anything that will come up from the Republicans in the Senate.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: We are at an inflection point in the fight for reproductive freedom and voting rights, and Democrats must stand together to protect these critical rights.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Black women will make history this year with historic gains in representation in political office.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: It doesn’t matter how big or small your race is, we’re here to help you run for office at EMILY’s List. https://www.emilyslist.org/run-to-win

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Happy International Women’s Day! I am committed to uplifting Democratic pro-choice women and making sure that our voices are heard — especially in politics. We belong at every level of government from school boards to Congress.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: A Monday mood.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Check out the podcast interview I did with The C Street in discussing increasing diversity representation in politics and the work we’re doing to protect reproductive freedom at EMILY’s List.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Claudette Colvin’s resistance as a young teenage girl is an inspiration to all. On this day in 1955, she was arrested for refusing to give up her bus seat to a white woman in Montgomery, Alabama. People like Claudette are a part of the reason why I want to bring EMILY’s List to where women are, who want to make positive change happen.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: “At EMILY's List, we have seen far too many history-makers and ground-breakers have their accomplishments questioned and their qualifications undermined. But we know what Jackson's example proves: to be the first and to break the mold, you bring qualifications, experience and character that is unrivaled. I am proud to support her and look forward to the legacy she will hopefully create on the court.”

name: Laphonza Butler
content: I was excited to learn about the amazing network that has given Judge Ketanji Brown Jackson support over her years in the legal field.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: A powerful message from Vice President Kamala Harris. Don’t let anything deter you from making positive change in your community.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Well said!“Our strength must not be underestimated, because, after all, it lies in our unity. And as we have always shown, it takes a lot more strength to build something up than it takes to tear something down.”— Vice President Kamala Harris

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Check out my interview with Aisha Mills on Black News Channel about the work we’re doing at EMILY's List to support women up and down the ballot for the midterms this November.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Yes. Don’t sit on the sidelines. We’re here to help you make progress at EMILY's List.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Black women make great business owners and great leaders. Let's elect more.

content: Tune in today at 4:30 p.m. EST for my discussion with A’shanti Gholar of The Brown Girls Guide on the EMILY’s List Instagram  https://www.instagram.com/emilys_list/

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Tomorrow, I’ll chat with The Brown Girls Guide founder A'shanti Gholar from the EMILY's List Instagram account. Give us a follow now so you get the alert when the conversation begins >> https://www.instagram.com/emilys_list

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Check out my upcoming #LeadersMatter Virtual Salon appearance next week with Emerge president A’shanti Gholar and Planned Parenthood Action Fund president Alexis McGill Johnson. I’m looking forward to an incredible discussion with these ladies.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Vice President Kamala Harris’s ambition should be celebrated instead of questioned. It is that same ambition that has inspired Democratic pro-choice women to run for office while juggling child care duties in the middle of a global pandemic.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: It was wonderful talking to A'Shanti Gholar on The Brown Girls Guide about my role at EMILY's List and our drive to elect even more Democratic pro-choice women to office this year in face of our current challenges.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: The first and not the last. So thrilling to see Jessica Watkins take to the stars as the first Black woman to spend months in space at the International Space Station!

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Today, Sandra Bland would be 35 years old. Her life mattered. We will never forget.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: We must protect and expand voting rights everywhere by making it easier, not harder to vote.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: I sat down with Simone Sebastian and Capital B News. We talked about what it takes to get more Black women in elected office, what we need in the midterms, and the ways Black women show up for our communities.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Happy birthday, Ellen Malcolm! I am so thankful for your guidance and your past leadership of EMILY’s List. I am committed to ensuring that we will elect even more Democratic pro-choice women to office everywhere.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Happy Lunar New Year to all who celebrate! It's the year of the Tiger, which represents courage and bravery, qualities that all of the EMILY's List endorsed women possess.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: I was happy to join the Campaign for Tobacco-Free Kids recently. Check out this clip!

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Both Rep. Val Demings and Cheri Beasley are pro-choice champions. They are ready to flip their seats from red to blue this coming November with your help.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: No matter what anti-choice Republicans say, a Black woman is qualified and ready to be a Supreme Court justice. I look forward to Madam Vice President Kamala Harris helping to confirm her to the Supreme Court.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Today we remember the 6 million victims and the survivors of the Holocaust. We stand strong against anti-semitism and all forms of bigotry. We cannot let hatred take control again.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: EMILY's List endorsed candidates that we’ve supported in their run for office made the decision to be heard and to have a seat at the table no matter what their socioeconomic status and ethnic background was. You can do the same as well.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Thank you, Rep. Barbara Lee for sharing how Shirley Chisholm inspired you to run for office and to lead.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Today is a good day to decide to run for office. We at EMILY's List are here to help you win:

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Madam Vice President Kamala Harris is exactly right on this. “We took an oath to preserve, protect, and defend the Constitution of the United States. And we will fight to protect a woman's right to choose. The constitutional right of women to make decisions about their own bodies is not an abstract concept. It saves women's lives.” — Vice President Kamala Harris

name: Laphonza Butler
content: One simply can’t exist without the other. We at EMILY's List are determined to protect both the right to the ballot box and the right to choose.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: On the 49th anniversary of Roe v. Wade, anti-choice Republicans are limiting access to abortion at the state level. That’s why we need Democratic pro-choice women like you to run for office. Join us: https://www.emilyslist.org/run-to-win

name: Laphonza Butler
content: “History tells us that we must keep fighting in order to see progress, so we must continue. And electing Democratic pro-choice Black women to the Senate is one way we do that.” - Laphonza Butler in Essence op-ed

name: Laphonza Butler
content: A year ago, millions of Americans witnessed history being made with the swearing-in of Madam Vice President Kamala Harris into office. She is our Vice President because of all the incredible women that have paved the way for generations.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: 2022 will be a crucially important year for Black women — and we’ll elect more to office by supporting them up and down the ballot.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: An update from our President Laphonza Butler on voting rights

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Today I’m reflecting on the legacy of Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. and the ongoing work to achieve his dream of justice and equality. We owe it to his legacy and those who paid the heaviest price to continue this mission until it’s realized.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: It’s Election Day! Let’s get out the vote for two of our EMILY’s List women, Jackie Hope Glass in Virginia and Lydia Edwards for State Senate in Massachusetts. We are thrilled to support them!

name: Laphonza Butler
content: I stand with Madam Vice President Kamala Harris in defense of democracy. I’m thrilled to see her take the fight on to protect democracy by working to ensure fair and free elections.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Many of our EMILY’s List women are serving in elected office amidst an unprecedented rise of threats of political violence. We are so proud of them and we will elect more like them to office this year.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: One year ago a violent mob of insurrectionists attacked the Capitol. The sexism and racism exhibited have roots in the misogyny and white supremacy that have long fueled violence in this country. Read our joint statement with The United State of Women and others here: https://usow.org/blog/jan6/

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Representation matters. We will work to elect even more women of color to office at every level of government in 2022. https://19thnews.org/.../nyc-city-council-women-majority.../

name: Laphonza Butler
content: I’m thankful to AFL-CIO President Liz Shuler for giving me the opportunity to discuss the role that women play in both labor advocacy and politics. We will elect even more Democratic pro-choice women in office to save democracy and protect voting rights & the right to choose.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Fifteen years ago today, Nancy Pelosi became the first woman speaker of the House. I am so thankful for her tenacious advocacy on behalf of the American people, and she continues to inspire us all in the work of electing more Democratic pro-choice women to office.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: If you weren’t engaged before, now is the time. There is a huge election later this year.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: If running for office is something you have thought about, make 2022 your year. Sign up today for Run to Win where we’ll teach you tips on how to run a great campaign. https://win.emilyslist.org/a/run_for_office

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Happy new year! I wish you and your loved ones the best in 2022.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Coming to EMILY's List was my biggest news of 2021. I’m excited to see what 2022 brings!

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Marco Rubio has got to go. Rep. Val Demings is a barrier-breaking leader who should be the next senator from Florida. It’s that simple.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Our team is trying to raise $200,000 before the year ends. Donate here to help elect women all year!

name: Laphonza Butler
content: So far, EMILY's List has endorsed ELEVEN governors up for election in 2022. Read their bios and donate a few dollars to your favorite.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: I hope everyone has a joyous Kwanzaa!

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Merry Christmas from my family to yours!

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Cheri Beasley has no viable opponents for the Democratic nomination for Senate in North Carolina. I know the South, and I know she can win this state. Learn more about her.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: So far at EMILY's List, we’ve endorsed NINE incredible women who can secure our Senate majority. Check out their bios (and drop a donation to them if you can).

content: This decision to permanently allow medication abortion by mail is long overdue. Medication abortion is extremely safe and people need full access to it, not restrictions.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: This was a fun and wonderful read about Stacey Abrams this morning.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: I stand with Madam Vice President Kamala Harris and couldn’t be more excited about the excellent work she is doing in office in service of the American people.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: This is a calculated attack that prevents people from accessing the reproductive health care that they need. It’s why we’ll be electing more Democratic pro-choice women at the state and local level in 2022 to defend abortion rights.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: We are proud to stand with Jessica Cisneros and her historic campaign in Texas’ 28th District.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: It’s why I’m counting on your support more than ever to help us win in 2022. We need to take back state legislatures, and expand the Democratic majority in Congress to help protect the right to choose.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: When we allow anti-choice politicians to interfere with the right to make medical decisions, we have to ask where it will end.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: I am grateful for the leadership and tenacity that Shirley Chisholm showed all these years ago in running for office. Happy birthday to Shirley Chisholm!

content: Carrie Meek was an excellent legislator who fought hard to rebuild her district after Hurricane Andrew. I will keep her family in my prayers.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Tune in this Sunday for a wonderful interview on Facebook Live with Holly J. Mitchell.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Happy Thanksgiving to you all from us at EMILY’s List. We’re so grateful for your support.

content: The huge expansions in wifi and public transit will improve education outcomes for at-risk kids and give working parents more time with their children. This bill is remarkable and Vice President Kamala Harris does a great job explaining it.

content: We are ready to elect more women like Kamala Harris  up and down the ballot this coming November!(photo credit: Gage Skidmore)

content: As a leader who came from the labor movement, I’m thrilled to see Vice President Kamala Harris leading on infrastructure and working to strengthen the union workforce in America.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: This is what a leader looks like!

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Speaker Pelosi has consistently delivered for the American people as speaker of the House. It matters a lot to have Democratic pro-choice women in positions of power. We will elect a lot more like her to office!

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Jackie Speier Thank you for your dedication and passion in fighting for families and upholding the right to choose in Congress. We're grateful for your service.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Don’t be afraid to be the first.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: This #TransAwarenessWeek, we’re so thankful that these incredible trans leaders have been elected to office with the help of EMILY's List. We stand ready to help more trans women run for office in 2022.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: To all the women out there considering a run for office, we’re here to help you take that first step at EMILY's List.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: We’re thrilled to support Marie Newman in her run for Illinois’ 6th Congressional District! She is a champion for reproductive rights, voting rights, gun violence prevention, and LGBTQ+ rights.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: On Tuesday, we added another Black Democratic pro-choice woman to the Democratic majority in Congress. We’re thrilled Rep. Shontel Brown is in office representing Ohioans!

name: Laphonza Butler
content: We won’t be deterred from electing more Democratic pro-choice women to office in 2022.“One thing Butler’s organizing experience taught her — through grinding campaigns, fierce opposition, reversals and slow-going, inch-by-inch progress — was persistence.”

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Shirley Chisholm helped change the world by being the first Black woman elected to Congress on this day in 1968. We are going to elect more Black women like Chisholm  to Congress.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Women in office pave the way for other women. It matters who we elect to office.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Today is your chance to elect more Democratic pro-choice women to office in:  City councils State legislatures CongressMake your voice heard today!

name: Laphonza Butler
content: I am so proud that 98 EMILY’s List women are running for office today on #ElectionDay! We can and we will flip & defend seats to protect reproductive rights for all. If you haven’t voted already, check your polling location and cast a vote for our EMILY’s List-endorsed candidates.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: To all the Democratic pro-choice women on the ballot this Nov. 2 — we’re rooting for you!

name: Laphonza Butler
content: We need more Democratic pro-choice women like you at the table. We're here to help you run for office at EMILY's List.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: I’ll be on Good Morning America's 3rd hour today to discuss the need to elect more Democratic pro-choice women to office. Check your local listings for the time.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: So grateful to see record numbers of Black women running, particularly since we are not at record numbers of Black women in office! I’m so proud EMILY's List is with several of these phenomenal candidates! Black women must be at the table. https://19thnews.org/.../black-women-candidates-2022.../

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Virginians -- have you made it out to vote yet? This election is going to be close, but we’ve endorsed a lot of fantastic women at EMILY’s List. See which ones are on your ballot!

name: Laphonza Butler
content: It’s been a little over a month, and I’m greatly enjoying the work at EL. Are you staying up to date on our recent endorsements and updates? If not, you should.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: I want all elected officials to know that they will have to defend their anti-choice stances in the midterms.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: In order to ensure that we build a world that is fair for everyone, we need to open the doors of power.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: This Voter Registration Day, I urge you to ensure that you’re registered to vote.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: We must do better to show all of America's daughters that they belong and are needed in political spaces.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: We must do more for women of color running for elected office. We will make EMILY’s List a home for all Democratic pro-choice women.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Hala Ayala is a staunch supporter of abortion rights, and she will be a key figure in defending those rights in Virginia.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: I am so proud of VP Harris. I was so proud to work for her on her presidential run, and I’m so proud of her now.

name: Laphonza Butler
content: “We have to maintain and grow Democratic majorities in Congress, in the House and in the Senate, and we have to win governor’s mansions and the state capitols, because that’s where some of the most harmful legislation to roll back the rights of everyday people in this country are taking place.” https://19thnews.org/2021/09/emilys-list-laphonza-butler/

name: Laphonza Butler
content: Thanks so much for all the well wishes. It really warmed my heart. I'm so grateful for this opportunity and excited to get to work!

name: Laphonza Butler
content: I am honored and excited to be joining EMILY's List as its new president! My entire career has centered around empowering women as they find their voices and make change. I have been proud to play a role in many victories with women leaders in my union SEIU Local 2015 and in politics, and I am excited to continue that work as the leader of EMILY's List.
